queries.query: CREATE TABLE `#__cb_songs` ( `song_id` int(10) NOT NULL auto_increment, `title` varchar(40) NOT NULL default '', `writer` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `song` text NOT NULL, `bpm` int(5) default NULL, `year` int(5) default NULL, `notes` text, `keywords` text, `copyrights` text, `chords` text NOT NULL, `category` int(5) NOT NULL default '0', `song_key` varchar(5) NOT NULL default '', `signature` varchar(10) default NULL, `rating` int(5) NOT NULL default '0', `views` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `ccli` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `add_time` int(15) NOT NULL default '0', `submitted_by` int(15) NOT NULL default '0', `order` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `published` tinyint(1) NOT NULL default '0', `words` text NOT NULL, `ref_code` varchar(20) NOT NULL default '', PRIMARY KEY (`song_id`), FULLTEXT KEY `song` (`song`), FULLTEXT KEY `notes` (`notes`) )

CREATE TABLE `#__cb_categories` ( `category_id` int(10) NOT NULL auto_increment, `title` varchar(40) NOT NULL default '', `order` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `published` tinyint(1) NOT NULL default '0', PRIMARY KEY (`category_id`) )

CREATE TABLE `#__cb_writers` ( `writer_id` int(10) NOT NULL auto_increment, `name` varchar(100) NOT NULL default '', `order` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `published` tinyint(1) NOT NULL default '0', PRIMARY KEY (`writer_id`) )

CREATE TABLE `#__cb_chords` ( `baseNote` int(11) NOT NULL default '0', `bassNote` int(11) NOT NULL default '-1', `signature` varchar(10) NOT NULL default '', `chord` int(11) NOT NULL default '0', `order` int(11) NOT NULL default '0', PRIMARY KEY (`baseNote`,`bassNote`,`signature`,`chord`) )

CREATE TABLE `#__cb_guitar_chords` ( `id` int(11) NOT NULL auto_increment, `note` int(11) default NULL, `bass` int(11) default NULL, `signature` varchar(10) default NULL, `fret` int(11) default NULL, `tab` varchar(6) default NULL, `fingers` varchar(6) default NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`id`) )
CREATE TABLE `#__cb_permissions` ( `id` int(10) NOT NULL auto_increment, `user_id` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `permission` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', PRIMARY KEY (`id`) )

CREATE TABLE `#__cb_sets` ( `set_id` int(10) NOT NULL auto_increment, `name` varchar(100) NOT NULL default '', `category` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `creator` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `songs` text NOT NULL, `comments` text NOT NULL, `views` int(10) NOT NULL default '0', `published` tinyint(1) NOT NULL default '1', PRIMARY KEY (`set_id`) )
